workflow.name: Smart Lead Qualification & Routing from Typeform to HubSpot with Data Enrichment
workflow.description:
### ‚úî Short Description
Automate your lead qualification pipeline ‚Äî capture Typeform Webhook leads, enrich with APIs, score intelligently, and route to HubSpot, Slack, and Sheets in real-time.

---

### üß© Description

Automate your lead management pipeline from form submission to CRM enrichment and routing.  
This workflow intelligently processes Typeform Webhook submissions, enriches leads using Hunter.io and Abstract API, scores them with dynamic logic, and routes them into HubSpot while keeping your sales team and tracking sheets up to date.

It‚Äôs a full-stack automation designed to turn raw form submissions into prioritized, qualified CRM-ready leads ‚Äî without manual intervention.

---

### üí° Who‚Äôs it for

- Marketing teams managing inbound leads from web forms  
- Sales operations teams that qualify and route leads  
- CRM administrators automating lead data entry and scoring  
- Automation professionals building data enrichment systems  

---

### ‚öôÔ∏è How it works / What it does

1. **Trigger:** Receives new Typeform Webhook submissions via Webhook.  
2. **Data Extraction:** Parses name, email, and company info.  
3. **Email Verification:** Validates email deliverability with Hunter.io.  
4. **Company Enrichment:** Fetches company data (industry, size, country) using Abstract API.  
5. **Lead Scoring Logic:** Calculates a lead score and assigns a *tier* (Hot / Warm / Cold).  
6. **Conditional Routing:**  
   - **Hot Leads (‚â•70)** ‚Üí Sent to HubSpot as *Qualified*.  
   - **Warm/Cold Leads (<70)** ‚Üí Sent to HubSpot as *Nurture* stage.  
7. **Revalidation Loop:**  
   - Waits (e.g., 3 days) ‚Üí Rechecks Nurture leads in HubSpot.  
   - Logs them to Google Sheets and alerts your Slack channel.  

---
![‚öôÔ∏è How it works _ What it does  visual selection.png](fileId:3128)
---

### üß∞ How to set up

1. **Connect accounts:**  
   - Typeform Webhook (for inbound lead capture)  
   - Hunter.io (API key for email verification)  
   - Abstract API (for company enrichment)  
   - HubSpot (via OAuth2 credentials)  
   - Slack (for notifications)  
   - Google Sheets (for logging)

2. **Customize the Webhook URL** inside your Typeform Webhook integration.  
3. **Replace API keys** with your own (Hunter.io, Abstract).  
4. **Adjust scoring logic** inside the `Lead Scoring & Routing Logic` node to fit your business.  
5. **Set Wait duration** (default: 10 seconds for testing ‚Üí change to 3 days for production).  
6. **Activate the workflow** and test it with a sample form submission.

---

### üîß Requirements

- Typeform account with webhook capability  
- Hunter.io account + API key  
- Abstract API account + API key  
- HubSpot account with OAuth2 credentials  
- Slack workspace & channel  
- Google Sheets integration  

---

### üé® How to customize the workflow

- **Scoring rules:** Modify the ‚ÄúLead Scoring & Routing Logic‚Äù node to adjust how points are calculated (e.g., country, industry, employee size).  
- **CRM target:** Replace HubSpot nodes with another CRM (e.g., Pipedrive, Salesforce).  
- **Notification channel:** Swap Slack for Email, Discord, or MS Teams.  
- **Data source:** Replace Typeform Webhook with another trigger like Webflow Forms, Airtable, or custom API input.  
- **Tracking:** Add Google Analytics or Notion API for additional reporting.

---

### üß≠ Summary

End-to-end lead automation workflow that combines **form data, enrichment APIs, CRM updates, and Slack alerts** into one intelligent system.  
Ideal for any team looking to centralize and qualify leads automatically ‚Äî from submission to sales.

parameters.content:
## üü¢ 1. Webhook Trigger
üß© Entry Point ‚Äî Receives form submissions from Typeform.

Accepts POST requests containing lead info.  
Webhook path: `/webhook/new-lead-webhook`

## üü¶ 2. Extract Lead Data
üß† Parses Typeform JSON to extract key fields:
- first_name  
- last_name  
- email  
- company  

Automatically derives the email domain for enrichment steps.

## 3.üü© Hunter.io Verification
‚úÖ Verifies lead email validity using the Hunter.io API.

Ensures only real and deliverable emails proceed to the next step.

## 4.üü® Extract Domain for Abstract
üß© Extracts the domain from the lead‚Äôs email address.

Used as input for the Abstract API enrichment request.

## 5.üüß Abstract Company Enrichment
üåê Calls Abstract API to enrich company details.

Fetches industry, employee count, location, and website metadata.

## 6.üü™ Lead Scoring & Routing Logic
üìä Calculates lead score based on:
- Company size
- Target country
- Industry match
- Domain type (business vs. free)
- LinkedIn presence

Assigns lead_tier: Cold / Warm / Hot.

## 7.üîµ IF High Priority
‚öôÔ∏è Decision Node ‚Äî Routes leads based on score:

‚úÖ TRUE (‚â•70): Qualified ‚Üí HubSpot (Qualified Path)  
‚ùå FALSE (<70): Nurture ‚Üí HubSpot (Nurture Path)

## 7.1 üü£ HubSpot Create Contact (Qualified)
üöÄ Creates ‚ÄúQualified‚Äù contact in HubSpot CRM.

Includes enrichment data, lead score, and lead stage = Qualified.

## 7.2 üü§ HubSpot Create Contact (Nurture)
üå± Creates ‚ÄúNurture‚Äù stage contact in HubSpot.

Used for lower-priority leads entering a recheck cycle.

## 7.2.1 üü† Wait (3 Days) ‚Üí ‚è≥ Delay for Nurture Recheck
‚è≥ Delays workflow for follow-up revalidation.

Current test delay: 10 seconds  
Production delay: 3 days

## 7.2.2 üî¥ HubSpot API Check ‚Üí üîç HubSpot Revalidation
üîç Queries HubSpot CRM for contacts still in Nurture stage.

Returns latest info like:
- Email
- Company
- Lead Score
- Lead Stage

## 7.2.2.1 üü¢ Slack Notification ‚Üí üì® Nurture Alert
üí¨ Sends Slack alert for leads still in NURTURE stage.

Includes:
üè¢ Company  
üìß Email  
üí• Lead Score  
üïí Timestamp

## 7.2.2.2 üü£ Google Sheets Logging ‚Üí üìä Nurture Log 
üìÑ Appends lead details to Google Sheet ‚ÄúNurture Follow-Up Log‚Äù.

Logs:
- Date
- Company
- Email
- Lead Score
- Stage

## üìù Workflow Summary Note
üß≠ Smart Lead Routing & Qualification System

Automates lead intake, enrichment, scoring, and CRM sync.
Ecosystem:

Typeform ‚Üí Hunter.io ‚Üí Abstract API ‚Üí HubSpot ‚Üí Slack ‚Üí Sheets

data.details: The Function node allows you to execute JavaScript in your workflow. Unlike the Function Item node, this node does not operate on incoming node data per-item. Instead, you must iterate over multiple items of incoming data yourself. This can be useful if you're performing data transformation where you want to manipulate the number of items being outputted by the node (i.e. 1 item is inputted in with nested object, 10 items are outputted without any nested objects)

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
